727694f-a.title: Queens: Prince Street - 36th Avenue
727694f-a.text:
Prince Street, adjoining the S.W. corner of 36th Avenue,
showing the Ebenezer Baptist Church.
P. L. Sperr  March 12, 1932

727699f-a.title: Queens: Prince Street - Northern Boulevard
727699f-a.text:
Prince Street, south from Northern Boulevard, showing old homes and the Ebenerer Baptist Church on the west side of the street and demolition on the east side. The buildings were torn down for the widening of Northern Boulevard.
P. L. Sperr  August 24, 1935

727576f-a.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - Prince Street
727576f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, south side, east from Prince to Main Streets, showing the demolition of this block of buildings for the widening of the thoroughfare. View 2 shows the same block after the Boulevard was widened and new buildings going up on the new building line.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: August 5, 1935
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 2: June 16, 1937

727577f-b.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - Prince Street
727577f-b.text:
Northern noulevard, north side, west from Prince Street. The building at the N. W. corner of Prince was erected after the boulevard was widened,anc stands on the site of the J. N. Merritt house of 1873. Views 2 anc 3 show the sSme area before the changes took place and show the Nerritt house (twin chimneys)
behind the taxpayer.
P. L. Sperr  View 1 May 30, 1938
NO hEPRODUCTIONS  View 2: October 18, 1936
View 3: July 10, 1936

727578f-b.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - Prince Street
727578f-b.text:
Northern Boulevard, at the N.E. corner of Prince Street, showing an old residence, owned by G.E. Carl in 1873. The building, together with others on both sides of the intersection,were later torn down when Northern Boulovard was widened.

727695f-a.title: Queens: Prince Street - 36th Avenue
727695f-a.text:
Prince Street, east side, at 36th Avenue, looking north and showing several old frame dwellings. Note the smoke coming out the chimney. These were torn down later, when
Northern Boulevard was widened.
P. L. Sperr  June 28, 1940
